sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Controller Manager
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Envoy as Envoy Sidecar<br/>8080/TCP mTLS
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>50051/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant REST as Model Registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over User,Controller: Flow 1: Create ModelRegistry CR
    User->>K8sAPI: POST ModelRegistry CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token/Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate CR<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>K8s API Server mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch Event<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Services, Routes<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources Created

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Access Model Registry (Istio + Gateway Mode)
    Client->>Route: GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3
    Route->>Gateway: Forward Request<br/>TLS1.3
    Gateway->>Envoy: HTTP Request<br/>mTLS ISTIO_MUTUAL
    Envoy->>Authorino: Auth Check<br/>gRPC mTLS<br/>Service Mesh Identity
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Authorized
    Authorino-->>Envoy: Auth OK
    Envoy->>REST: Forward Request<br/>HTTP plaintext (localhost)
    REST->>DB: Query Model Metadata<br/>PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>TLS1.2+ (optional)<br/>Password/Client Cert
    DB-->>REST: Query Results
    REST-->>Envoy: JSON Response
    Envoy-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Controller,REST: Flow 3: Operator Metrics Collection
    Controller->>Controller: Expose Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (localhost)
